Author the manifest.json entry for a new example site named "__NAME__" in this
repository (hwaro-examples). This is the art-direction step — no site code is
written here. The entry you produce is the complete assignment a cheaper
builder model will execute, so every field must be decided and precise.

Read first: DESIGN.md §1-2 and §15 steps 1-2, then AGENTS.md "Tag vocabulary",
then the hwaro-design skill appended at the end of this prompt. DESIGN.md
governs this collection's own constraints (the diversity matrix, manifest
shape, process); the skill is the upstream, actively-maintained source for
taste calls DESIGN.md doesn't spell out — dial calibration (variance/motion/
density), palette and typography discipline, anti-slop tells. Where the two
conflict on a collection-specific rule (e.g. font-pairing cap, hue-distance
floor), DESIGN.md wins.

Process:
1. Confirm the name "__NAME__" is legal: not in manifest.json, not in
   scripts/retired-names.txt, not a reserved word (see DESIGN.md §15.1),
   matches ^[a-z][a-z0-9]*$. If it is illegal, STOP and report why instead
   of inventing a different name.
2. Analyze the collection for gaps before choosing anything:
   - category distribution and scheme balance (manifest.json)
   - font pairings at the 5-use cap (count every display/text pair; choose
     one from the DESIGN.md §5 pool with 4 or fewer uses)
   - accent hues already used in your chosen category+scheme bucket (keep
     >= 10 degrees of hue distance)
   - layouts and signatures in the chosen category (your signature must be
     unique collection-wide; prefer under-used layouts)
3. Write the complete entry, matching the exact JSON shape of existing
   entries: name, title, description (20-140 chars, gallery-ready), category,
   scheme, styles (1-2), brief (a vivid, concrete paragraph the builder can
   execute without judgment — name the bands of the homepage in order),
   typography {display, text, mono}, palette (+palette_dark for auto/dark
   sites), layout, signature (one distinctive, CSS-implementable move stated
   concretely), content {theme, sections, standalone}, features.
   The content plan must yield 6-10 markdown files.
4. Palette discipline: compute WCAG contrast for fg/bg, muted/bg, accent/bg,
   accent_fg/accent — all must be >= 4.5. State the computed ratios in your
   report. No pure #000/#fff in dark palettes; desaturate the dark accent.
5. INSERT the entry into manifest.json in alphabetical order by name. This is
   strictly additive: never modify, rename, or delete any existing entry, and
   never reuse another entry's brief/palette/signature with the name swapped —
   a near-duplicate of an existing entry is a hard failure (§13 "no recolored
   clones"), even if the validator passes.
6. Run scripts/validate-manifest.py — it must exit 0 with no new warnings.

Report: the inserted entry verbatim, the contrast ratios, the pairing use
count, the hue distances in the bucket, and the validator output.
Do NOT create examples/__NAME__/ and do NOT git commit — manifest entry only.

